\begin_layout Proposition
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "prop:The-available-case"

\end_inset

The available case estimator is strongly consistent if either
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
The raters are exchangeable and data is missing pairwise completely at random.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The raters are not exchangeable and data is missing uniformly at random.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Proposition
The estimator is in general not consistent when data is missing at random,
 even when raters are exchangeable.
 Moreover,
 the standard errors calculated using the usual machinery are correct.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Remark
A weaker condition but arguably useless condition suffices for consistency with exchangeable raters.
 See the proof for details.
\end_layout

