\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Weighted available-case estimator
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The consistency conditions for the PAC estimator suggests the following variant:
 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\kappa}_{C}=1-\hat{d}/\hat{d}_{C}$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\hat{d} & = & \frac{\sum_{i=1}^{n}\sum_{j<k}l(X_{ij}^{\star},X_{ik}^{\star})M_{ij}M_{ik}\pi_{jk}^{-1}}{\sum_{i=1}^{n}\sum_{j<k}M_{ij}M_{ik}\pi_{jk}^{-1}},\quad\hat{d}_{C}=\frac{\sum_{i,i'}\sum_{j<k}l(X_{ij}^{\star},X_{i'k}^{\star})M_{ij}M_{i'k}\pi_{j}^{-1}\pi_{k}^{-1}}{\sum_{i,i'}\sum_{j<k}M_{ij}M_{i'k}\pi_{j}^{-1}\pi_{k}^{-1}}.
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

It should be clear that 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\kappa}_{C}$
\end_inset

 is consistent when the data is missing PMCAR,
 exchangeable raters or not.
\end_layout

